, or engineering management . UIC MIE is a vibrant and diverse community of students, researchers, and professionals, and we are excited about the prospect of you joining us.  One important thing to know is that admission to our undergraduate programs is handled through UIC’s main undergraduate admissions office , so we encourage you to visit its site if you have not already done so. If you are looking for information on how and when to apply, details on financial aid, and a link to the online application, that is where you will find it.  We invite you explore this entire department website to learn more about mechanical and industrial engineering at the University of Illinois at Chicago.      important links           Mechanical engineering major  Be a creator. Mechanical engineering teaches you to design, prototype, test, and create machinery.             Industrial engineering major  Master processes and systems as an industrial engineer. Gain the insight needed to enhance production and workflow.             Engineering management major  Fuse the technological edge of an engineering degree with the business acumen that comes from the study of management.             UIC admissions  This is where you can get all the information you need about application procedures—and where you can apply.             The College  MIE is one of six departments in UIC’s College of Engineering. Learn more about the College on our main site.             ME and IE overview  The advantages of our ME and IE majors—in two brief pages.          Helpful Links for Future Students        Admission requirements  Find out what you need to get your start at UIC Engineering.          Transfer applicants  Coming to UIC Engineering from another university? Start here.          International applicants  Visit UIC Global's site, our welcome center for prospective international students.           ABET Accreditation   Our undergraduate programs in mechanical engineering and industrial engineering are accredited by ABET, the Accreditation Board for Engineering and Technology .  ABET is the recognized accreditor for college and university programs in applied science, computing, engineering, and technology. It is a federation of 28 professional and technical societies representing these fields. Among the most respected accreditation organizations in the United States, ABET has provided leadership and quality assurance in higher education for more than 75 years.  Learn more about ABET accreditation in UIC MIE.          Undergraduate    Back to main content           Admitted Students    Admissions    Accreditation    Courses    ME Major    IE Major    EM Major    Minors    Internships and Jobs    Student Groups    Student Profiles    Student Resources                   UIC Logo         College Of  Engineering           Quicklinks    Faculty Resources    Graduate Resources    Undergraduate Resources    ABET Accreditation    Contact UIC MIE         Contact   Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering  2039 Engineering Research Facility, 842 W. Taylor St., Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-5317  Fax: (312) 413-0447  mie@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 